p:
9. Thus far: three possible meanings of “appearance.” These three must be kept distinct:

 1. something that shows up indirectly through something else (e.g., a disease, which manifests itself indirectly
through a symptom);

 2. that through which something else shows up indirectly while remaining hidden (e.g., the rash as manifesting a
hidden disease);

 3. a phenomenon in the genuine sense of what-directly-shows-itself.
